&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FIXED TERM 2 YEARS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brief Description of the Role: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a role within clinical research in the Trust to provide effective senior clinical nursing leadership This post is an important part of the development, promotion and support of research, particularly clinical research within the Trust and will act in a co-ordinating role for the research workforce (i.e. nurses and admin staff), working with CBUs to help manage their research delivery teams and ensure that the research workforce works collectively and flexibly to deliver the Trust’s research objectives and meets its performance targets. The post-holder will also be required to champion the profile of the research delivery workforce across the Trust, showcasing the positive contribution they make to the services of the Trust as well as the patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Summary of most important Experience/Skills/Qualifications required:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must possess substantial management/ leadership experience of clinical research at senior nurse/ midwife level including working on clinical trials with an expert understanding of clinical research issues, management and governance and current issues in NHS research. It is essential that the post-holder be adaptable, resourceful and able to demonstrate the experience required to oversee a large and complex workforce based across the Trust. Management of change and the ability to work within a multi-disciplinary context are essential to the job. The successful candidate will be a registered nurse/ midwife with a research qualification or at least 4 years of clinical experience in a research setting; they will have a professional manner, have a flexible approach to work and be able to work independently using their own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal Enquiries to:&lt;/strong&gt; Dr Tracy Watson, Director of Research Operation on Tel: 01274 382342 / 07855 820187&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer staff gymnasiums on both hospital sites, excellent pension scheme and advice on childcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 09.11.20 (This date may change dependent on the response)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 17.11.20 – week commencing 30.11.20&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
